The paper focuses on building generative models for natural source code, which involves learning a distributed representation of source code elements and incorporating both sequential and hierarchical structure. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions integrating closely with a compiler, which suggests that it may also belong to the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses refining how the model generates identifier tokens based on what variables are currently in scope, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques for source code, which suggests that it may also belong to the computational linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
